    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in NAS EMM/ESM cause decoding functions\n\n### Summary\nThe NAS decoding functions for EMM/ESM causes and KSI sequence numbers were missing proper buffer length validation, potentially leading to buffer overflows when processing malformed messages.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EmmCause.c`: Added length checking before buffer access\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EsmCause.c`: Added length checking before buffer access  \n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/KsiAndSequenceNumber.c`: Added length checking before buffer access\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen processing NAS messages with truncated IE payloads, these functions would attempt to read beyond the provided buffer boundary, causing undefined behavior. This can be observed when:\n1. Receiving a NAS message with an EMM cause IE that has insufficient data\n2. The decode function attempts to read the cause value without verifying buffer length\n3. Results in memory access violation or corrupted data interpretation\n\nThe fix ensures proper buffer bounds checking is performed before any data access, returning appropriate error codes when buffer length is insufficient.\n"
}